children.summary: Get a flag to indicate whether test cases with no data should be skipped (instead of failed, which is the default behavior).

summary: Indicates a test case which delays enumeration of tests until execution time.
remarks: This is normally used when theory data enumeration is performed at execution time, either because theory data pre-enumeration was disabled, or data found during discovery was not serializable.
